Okay, so BOOM! ✨Now that I have your attention with my scroll-stopping glow…let’s get into these health facts! 👉🏾

Earlier this month, I ran into some information that is not that common to talk about in public but is important for our health. 

So, here we go. More than 80% of sexually active women and men will get HPV in their lifetime. Not sure why something so common makes us so uncomfortable. 🤷🏾‍♀️

Anyhow…

One way to prevent HPV is by getting the HPV vaccine. Did you know the vaccine can also help prevent you from getting cervical cancer? The #HPVvaccine has been around since 2006, and even though there are a lot of myths about the vaccine, the fact is that it is entirely safe! 

Some facts about the HPV vaccine that are less well-known: 
* If you have had HPV, you can still get the vaccine.
* Women and men can get the HPV vaccine from ages 9 to 45. 
* The HPV vaccine can help prevent six types of cancer, including cervical cancer.

If you want to know more about the HPV vaccine, go to @sharecancersupport. SHARE has reliable information about the HPV vaccine and much more!

#SHARECancerSupport #CervicalCancerAwarenessMonth

Starting this month with a level one chemical peel at @OVMEOfficial! 

For the last several months, I’ve had the worst stress acne I have ever experienced in my ENTIRE 30 years of life — painful breakouts that were practically uncontrollable. Usually I don’t mind rocking a fresh face, but this left me feeling a bit self-conscious without covering up the breakouts. 

Although I’d been using some of the best medical grade skincare daily and keeping up with my med spa appointments, I knew this (along with other reactions my body was experiencing) would never clear if I didn’t actually remove the stressors from my daily life…and I recently did just that. 

I’m excited to continue my healthy skincare journey at OVME and finally get back on track with the help of the ladies at Legacy West! ✨🧖🏾‍♀️

🗣️Freelance does not mean “free” or “cheap” labor. 🙅🏾‍♀️ It is a form of self-employment defined as working for different companies at different times rather than being permanently employed by one.

They are still professionals and business owners who have spent a lot of time and money on education, equipment, etc. to constantly enhance their skills and the quality of the product/service they provide…and many have rates that reflect those factors. 

Treat them with the same respect that you would with any other professional you sit at the table with. ✌🏾 #freelanceisntfree

✨Embracing the Journey of Freedom✨A few months ago, I bid farewell to a toxic corporate world and fully embraced the path of a full-time freelance creative. While I’m no stranger to freelancing and entrepreneurship, this time feels different. 

This time, I have a fresh perspective. I’ve had a lot of time to re-evaluate, invest in myself, ask God for guidance, remember who I am, and understand my worth (that’s a major one). I’m going all in and no longer playing it safe.

The decision to break free from the chains of routine and step into the realm of limitless possibilities was both daunting and exhilarating. I'm ready to breathe life into my passions, explore my creativity, and turn my dreams into reality. Grateful for the lessons learned (all of them) and excited for the new adventures ahead. This is a journey where passion meets purpose and dreams soar high. 🦋

Learned that Lady Suite is closing this past week and I’m really going to miss them. 🥺 I remember seeing their Botanical Oil on Instagram (back in 2018) and thinking, “I HAVE to try that!” That was before all of the indie beauty stores where more widespread and a lot of these brands were in small boutiques or select stores. 

During a family trip to Denver, I tracked down a boutique/salon that carried the Botanical Oil and purchased it. I continued to use and share my love for the brand over the years and it is still the only intimate skincare brand I use.

Through my own journey, the ladies of @ladysuite_beauty have always been extremely supportive of my endeavors. Recently, I was able to shoot for Lady Suite and it feels like a full circle moment to me. Back then, I was just snapping product photos of the product for my beauty blog reviews (see carousel photos 4 & 5). Now, five years later, I’ve been able to work with them as a photographer (first 3 photos)…and the growth is real!

Thank you for trusting me with your vision and working with me on this project! It may seem small, but it really means A LOT that you considered me. I’m going to miss y’all, but I wish you the very BEST in the next part of your journeys! 💖 Jaleesa
